Three-ME (Multi-sector Macroeconomic Model for the Evaluation of Environmental
 and Energy policy) is a new model of the French economy developed by the
 ADEME, OFCE and TNO.
 Its main purpose is to evaluate the impact of environmental and energy
 policy measures on the economy at the macroeconomic and sectoral levels.
 Moreover it has the ambition to overcome the two limitation of standard
 top-down CGEM pointed above by introducing neo-Keynesian features such
 as inertia in price and quantities and bottom-up features in the modeling
 of consumption behavior.
